        public SpeedLimit getNearestSpeedLimit(java.lang.String path)
                                throws ApiException
        Gets NearestSpeedLimit GetNearestSpeedLimit Endpoint will take point coordinates of a path and will return the posted speed limit of the road segment on which this path will snap.
        Parameters:
        path - Accepts multiple points which will be snapped to the nearest road segment. Longitude and Latitude will be comma separated (longitude,latitude) and Point Coordinates will be separated by semi-colon(;) (required)
        Returns:
        SpeedLimit
